<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Commercial Banking (GCB) is the leading commercial bank in the U.S., serving one out of three companies with revenues of between $2.5 million and several billion dollars.  GCB generates more than $10 billion in annual revenue and $4 billion in net income from a variety of market-leading capital raising and treasury businesses. It serves more than 155,000 corporate clients through dedicated client teams who provide seamless, integrated delivery of the bank&#39;s full capabilities. GCB associates offer clients unrivaled market access, flexibility and value through our core businesses.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Global Product Solutions (GPS) designs, delivers and services integrated credit and treasury products to more than 140,000 clients around the world, including small businesses, middle-market and large corporations, multi-nationals, financial institutions and governments. These solutions, distributed through client managers, include business and corporate lending, global payments and liquidity management, commercial card services, trade finance, foreign exchange, lines of credit and equipment finance solutions. GPS is the number one treasury services provider in the United States and a leading provider globally, serving 95 percent of U.S. Fortune 500 companies and 73 percent of the Global Fortune 500.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The program is designed to build strong talent for client-facing roles in Global Commercial Banking and Global Product Solutions. Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America offers paid internship opportunities and a dynamic environment in which to build a strong financial services career.   
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Candidates must be pursuing bachelor&#39;s degree in business, finance and/or accounting. Candidates must have a demonstrated record of achievement, such as extracurricular activities or leadership roles. Some common driving characteristics include: finance knowledge, excellent verbal and written communication skills, personal leadership, the ability to inspire a strong sense of camaraderie and technical skills such as Excel and PowerPoint.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Positions are available in major markets across the Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America footprint. Line-of-business and location assignment is based on business need and candidate interest.
</p>

